                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2605.06548/2605.06548v1/x25.png",
                "caption": "Figure 10:Overall scaling performance under a unified few-shot generative evaluation protocol.Across eight benchmarks and Task Average,𝒞​o​l​a\\mathcal{C}olaDLMexhibits strong scaling dynamics, ultimately reaching the best average performance. It should be noted that the lower absolute accuracy observed on specific multiple-choice tasks is an anticipated consequence of the rigorous generative evaluation paradigm; nevertheless, the underlying scaling trends are robustly preserved. These findings imply that continuous latent prior modeling possesses significant scaling potential, rendering the current performance a conservative measure of its true capacity.",
